Commentary Text: Shami to Dwayne Smith, out Dwayne Smith Run Out!! Is Dwayne Smith short there at the bowler's end? Yes he is. He was a sloth there, has to pay in the end. Got hurried on the short ball and mistimed the pull to short fine leg. Ishan Kishan wanted the single and set off. Commentary Text: Basil Thampi to Corey Anderson, out Corey Anderson Run Out!! Third run out of the innings. Once again it's the rocket from Rajkot. Why do you take a chance against him? He is so good there. Coming to the ball, it was a short of length delivery just outside off, Anderson chops the cut to backward point and wanders out of his crease for a non-existent single. He is sent back by his partner. By the time he turns back and tries to return, Jaddu does the thing he often does. Finding the target direct at the striker's end. Corey Anderson run out (Jadeja) 6(6) [4s-1]

Slower ball from Faulkner, Iyer taps it towards backward point again, a little bit in front of the fielder this time and they decide to go through for the single. The man they are taking on is Ravindra Jadeja, one of the best fielders in this tournament, and if he hits, more often than not his arm will catch you short. Samuels is a yard out. Samuels run out (Jadeja) 1(4)

Commentary Text: Sangwan to Pant, out Pant Run Out!! Waste, a complete waste. Pant has had a brainfade. He's completely caught up in the LBW call, so much so that he forgets to plonk his bat inside the crease. Excellent comeback from Sangwan, spearing it full on leg, Pant plays across the line and it appears to hit him on the back leg. Maybe an inside edge, maybe going down leg, whatever it is, it isn't out. Meanwhile, Pant is anxious about the decision, wanders out of the crease and Raina capitalizes from slip. Pant run out (Raina) 4(2) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: D Kulkarni to Samson, FOUR, that's as minimal footwork as you'd get, and the ball has sped to the boundary at the rate of knots. What timing. What a start. Shows you how good a pitch this is as well. Back of a length from Kulkarni, curling away a touch outside off, and Samson just caresses it from the crease through the covers
